<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,705,948]" pageId="7" pageNumber="576">
This species was described based on specimens (sex not informed) from 
<collectingCountry box="[984,1073,706,732]" name="Panama" pageId="7" pageNumber="576">Panama</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion box="[1089,1189,705,732]" country="Panama" name="Chiriqui" pageId="7" pageNumber="576">Chiriquí</collectingRegion>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Chemsak, J. A. &amp; Linsley, E. G." pageId="7" pageNumber="576" pagination="404 - 417" refId="ref8188" refString="Chemsak, J. A. &amp; Linsley, E. G. (1970) Additional designations of lectotypes of Neotropical Cerambycidae in the collections of the British Museum (Natural History) (Coleoptera). Journal of the Kansas Entomological Society, 43 (4), 404 - 417." type="journal article" year="1970">Chemsak &amp; Linsley (1970)</bibRefCitation>
designated a 
<typeStatus box="[380,486,741,767]" pageId="7" pageNumber="576">lectotype</typeStatus>
. Interestingly, despite the similarity with 
<taxonomicName authority=", Bates (1885)" authorityName=", Bates" authorityYear="1885" box="[952,1246,741,768]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Leptostylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="576" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="orbiculus">
<emphasis box="[952,1088,741,767]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="576">L. orbiculus</emphasis>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Bates, H. W." box="[1102,1246,741,768]" pageId="7" pageNumber="576" pagination="249 - 436" refId="ref8053" refString="Bates, H. W. (1885) s. n. Biologia Centrali-Americana, Insecta, Coleoptera, Supplement to Longicornia, 5, 249 - 436." type="journal article" year="1885">Bates (1885)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
did not compare the two species. The most reliable difference between them is the presence of two centrobasal crests on each elytron in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bates" authorityYear="1885" box="[180,328,813,839]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Leptostylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="576" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quintalbus">
<emphasis box="[180,328,813,839]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="576">L. quintalbus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[343,424,813,839]" captionStart="FIGURES 15–21" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1874,1898]" captionTargetBox="[163,1428,438,1848]" captionTargetId="figure-119@6.[151,1436,426,1850]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 15–21. Leptostylus spp. 15–17) Leptostylus orbiculus Bates, 1880, male: 15) Dorsal habitus; 16) Lateral habitus; 17) Head, frontal view. 18–21) Leptostylus quintalbus Bates, 1885, male: 18) Head, frontal view; 19) Dorsal habitus; 20) Ventral habitus; 21) Lateral habitus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4612815" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4612815/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="576">Fig. 18</figureCitation>
) and only one in 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Bates" authorityYear="1885" box="[620,756,813,839]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Leptostylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="576" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="orbiculus">
<emphasis box="[620,756,813,839]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="576">L. orbiculus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[771,854,813,839]" captionStart="FIGURES 15–21" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1874,1898]" captionTargetBox="[163,1428,438,1848]" captionTargetId="figure-119@6.[151,1436,426,1850]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 15–21. Leptostylus spp. 15–17) Leptostylus orbiculus Bates, 1880, male: 15) Dorsal habitus; 16) Lateral habitus; 17) Head, frontal view. 18–21) Leptostylus quintalbus Bates, 1885, male: 18) Head, frontal view; 19) Dorsal habitus; 20) Ventral habitus; 21) Lateral habitus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4612815" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4612815/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="576">Fig. 17</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
